{"TopicId":150311,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Bug hunt","CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-18T20:43:06Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-18T20:43:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi all,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0So I am getting to grips with 1.2 having not looked at the prerelease and I have found two bugs so far. One to do with rover wheels breaking but that one needs more testing and one I can reproduce which I don\u0027t think has been found yet.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0When you use the in-game settings menu fairings disappear when you click apply, so anytime you change a setting in-game the fairings disappear. Can anyone else confirm?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gameslinx","CreatedById":144828,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-18T21:27:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan confirm this happened to me once but I just assumed I deleted the fairing myself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother bug is that there are gaps in the runway and tiny but annoying gaps in planetary surfaces. That really needs addressing as it flips up my SSTOs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-19T12:32:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222811568\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022150311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476826055\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144828\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gamel0rd1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, Gamel0rd1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan confirm this happened to me once but I just assumed I deleted the fairing myself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK thanks, can someone else confirm they see this? I don\u0027t want to report it until I know it is prevalent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-19T12:32:34Z\u0022 title=\u002210/19/2016 12:32  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 19, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Majorjim!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Waxing_Kibbous","CreatedById":151611,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-19T13:16:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGoing to need some better steps to follow, simplest craft possible, is what scene, etc. Just tried it on the launchpad with a command pod in a fairing with no issues.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-19T13:19:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHmm, I\u0027m out right now but will have another\u00A0look when I get back. All I had to do, at any time in\u00A0game was click apply in the settings tab and all fairings disappeared from the craft. Bases remained. I will try with a single fairing this eve and report back.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-10-19T13:20:14Z\u0022 title=\u002210/19/2016 01:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 19, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Majorjim!\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoctorDavinci","CreatedById":150019,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-19T13:38:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222812433\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022150311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476880339\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002261954\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim!\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Majorjim! said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK thanks, can someone else confirm they see this? I don\u0027t want to report it until I know it is prevalent.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can confirm this ... I have experienced it a couple times when adjusting the master volume\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHappens every time I click apply in the settings menu\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpannerMonkey(smce)","CreatedById":50907,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-10-19T13:53:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222811568\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022150311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221476826055\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022144828\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gamel0rd1\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Gamel0rd1 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan confirm this happened to me once but I just assumed I deleted the fairing myself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother bug is that there are gaps in the runway and tiny but annoying gaps in planetary surfaces. That really needs addressing as it flips up my SSTOs\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI reported this to the